"title": "1660: Sermon on the Mount",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1660: sermon on the mount",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A collection of Jesus Christ's teaching on the theme of discipleship. It deals with the righteousness required of disciples, the way they are to perform their religious duties, and the blessing and persecution they will know as followers of Christ. It can be seen as a manifesto setting out the nature of life in the kingdom of God.</p>\n<h2>The setting of the Sermon on the Mount</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:1\">MAT 5:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:17\">LUK 6:17</a></strong> <em>Either Jesus Christ taught similar material in two different locations, as is common in preaching, or else Luke more specifically identifies that he taught on a level place or plateau on the mountainside.</em></p>\n<h2>The teaching of the Sermon on the Mount</h2>\n<h3>The blessings of being in the kingdom</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:3-Matt5:12\">MAT 5:3–5:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:20-Luke6:23\">LUK 6:20–6:23</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's disciples are to have a positive influence on the world</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:13-Matt5:16\">MAT 5:13–5:16</a></p>\n<h3>The relationship between Jesus Christ's message and the law</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17-Matt5:21\">MAT 5:17–5:21</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's disciples are to exhibit a new depth of righteousness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:20\">MAT 5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:48\">MAT 5:48</a></p>\n<h3>The righteousness required of Jesus Christ disciples</h3>\n<p>Not only murder but also anger and broken relationships are wrong:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:21-Matt5:24\">MAT 5:21–5:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:13\">EXO 20:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25-Matt5:26\">MAT 5:25–5:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:58-Luke12:59\">LUK 12:58–12:59</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:27-Matt5:30\">MAT 5:27–5:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:14\">EXO 20:14</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:31-Matt5:32\">MAT 5:31–5:32</a> <em>faithfulness in marriage is called for</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:33-Matt5:37\">MAT 5:33–5:37</a> <em>faithfulness in speech is called for</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:38-Matt5:48\">MAT 5:38–5:48</a> <em>Retaliation must be abandoned, and enemies as well as neighbours must be loved.</em></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's disciples are to seek only God's approval in their religious duties</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:1\">MAT 6:1</a></strong></p>\n<h3>How religious duties are to be performed</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:2-Matt6:4\">MAT 6:2–6:4</a> <em>Giving to the poor is to be done secretly</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:5-Matt6:8\">MAT 6:5–6:8</a> <em>Prayer is not to become a public display</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:16-Matt6:18\">MAT 6:16–6:18</a> <em>Fasting is to be done without show.</em></p>\n<h3>The kingdom is to be valued above material possessions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:19-Matt6:21\">MAT 6:19–6:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:24-Matt6:34\">MAT 6:24–6:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:22-Luke12:31\">LUK 12:22–12:31</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's disciples are to avoid being judgmental</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:1-Matt7:2\">MAT 7:1–7:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:3-Matt7:5\">MAT 7:3–7:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:41-Luke6:42\">LUK 6:41–6:42</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's disciples should pray, confident of an answer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:7-Matt7:8\">MAT 7:7–7:8</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:9-Luke11:10\">LUK 11:9–11:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:9-Matt7:12\">MAT 7:9–7:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:11-Luke11:13\">LUK 11:11–11:13</a></p>\n<h3>A pattern for prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:9-Matt6:15\">MAT 6:9–6:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:2-Luke11:4\">LUK 11:2–11:4</a></p>\n<h3>True disciples will obey Jesus Christ teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:21\">MAT 7:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:15-Matt7:20\">MAT 7:15–7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:24-Matt7:27\">MAT 7:24–7:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:47-Luke6:49\">LUK 6:47–6:49</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of Jesus Christ's teaching in the Sermon on the Mount</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:28-Matt7:29\">MAT 7:28–7:29</a></strong></p>",
